title: HealthTap - Telehealth Doctors
description: HealthTap is a telehealth app that revolutionizes primary care by providing ongoing, affordable care with a dedicated, online primary care doctor you love. With or without insurance, HealthTap is your go-to solution for personalized medical care that saves you time and money. Find the best online doctors with HealthTap, and schedule your doctor appointment same-day or same-week!Enjoy the convenience of meeting your primary care doctor regularly for health checkups, prescriptions, lab tests, results, treatment plans, and specialist referrals. Our top U.S. board-certified doctors, available for virtual telehealth appointments 7 days a week across all 50 states, focus on building long-lasting, trusted relationships with their patients, ensuring comprehensive healthcare for Americans.MEMBERSHIP BENEFITSFor just $15/month* (billed annually), enjoy significant savings and:• Same-day or weekly video telehealth appointments with your primary care virtual doctor for $44/visit or less**• Free text consultations with your doctor for follow-ups and clarifications• Access to the first available doctor during off-hours and while traveling out-of-state for urgent care at $59/visit or less**• Prescriptions, lab tests, specialist referrals, and doctor's notes for school or work• Up to 75% off prescriptions with local pharmacy coupons• No additional cost for setting up child profilesWe accept numerous healthcare insurance plans, HSA/FSA cards, and some insurance plans may cover your membership.*Membership may be covered by select insurance plans**Insurance coverage may reduce your out-of-pocket costNON-MEMBERSHIP OPTIONS$129 Urgent Care Telehealth Doctor Visits: Consult the first available doctor within minutes (7 days a week) via telemedicine video or text for advice, prescriptions, test orders, and referrals. Pay just $129 per visit (retail price) or your insurance copay.FREE Educational Doctor Answers: Get text responses to your health questions from our network of over 90,000 U.S. doctors across 147 specialties who volunteer their time to help millions like you for FREE! Search millions of answers or post your own for responses from real doctors within hours.CONDITIONS WE TREATOur telehealth and telemedicine services cover a wide range of medical issues, including:• Chronic condition management (diabetes, asthma, etc…)• Women's health• Children's health (ages 2+)• Men's health• Senior health (ages 65+)• Wellness & prevention• Sexual health• Mental & behavioral health…and much more!MEMBER TESTIMONIALSRead what our members say about the convenience, affordability, and quality of HealthTap's telehealth and telemedicine primary care services.“Great prices, very friendly doctor, very convenient, and I was able to get a same or next-day appointment and prescriptions that I needed.” – Joe C“Super quick and efficient. Doctor was very personable and made me feel comfortable through the telehealth visit. She explained everything and made sure I understood.”  – Katlyn A“When I moved I lost my medical insurance.  I found HealthTap and it was a lifesaver.  I have told many people about it.” – Steven B“My doctor is extremely accommodating. She has multiple appointment times open throughout the weekend. She is never in a hurry and very thorough. HealthTap is a wonderful service!” – Diana C100% SECURE & CONFIDENTIALWe prioritize your medical privacy. Your consultation with the doctor is confidential and HIPAA compliant.NEED HELP?For responsive and helpful support, contact us at support@healthtap.com.

title: Salud Andalucía
description: Salud Andalucía es una aplicación que le da acceso a toda información del Sistema Sanitario Público de Andalucía (SSPA) y agrupa las apps que el SSPA dispone para el conjunto de los usuarios. La aplicación incluye una sección específica sobre el coronavirus COVID-19.El uso de esta aplicación no sustituye la relación médico-paciente.Para cualquier consulta de la información ofrecida por la aplicación puede ponerse en contacto a través del siguiente enlace: https://www.sspa.juntadeandalucia.es/servicioandaluzdesalud/ciudadania/reclamaciones-sugerencias-y-agradecimientosPolítica de privacidadhttps://www.sspa.juntadeandalucia.es/servicioandaluzdesalud/politica-de-privacidadAviso legalhttps://www.sspa.juntadeandalucia.es/servicioandaluzdesalud/aviso-legal

title: OpenWHO: Knowledge for Health
description: OpenWHO is the World Health Organization's (WHO) interactive knowledge-transfer platform offering online courses to improve the response to health emergencies. OpenWHO enables the Organization and its key partners to transfer life-saving knowledge to large numbers of frontline responders.With OpenWHO, you have the flexibility to learn at your convenience. Watch the short video lectures and test your knowledge with self-tests when and where you like. The course forum and the collaboration space allow you to get in touch with other participants and experts around the world. Designed primarily for health care workers, frontline responders, and decision-makers, the app is also a source of information for those affected by disease outbreaks and health emergencies, or for those with a general interest in WHO's work in health emergencies. It features 6 channels:- The Outbreak channel addresses the management of infectious diseases and provides life-saving, scientific information.- The Ready for Response channel helps prepare personnel who are training for deployment to work in disease outbreaks and health emergencies.- The Get Social channel focuses on social science-based interventions and helps to communicate with affected communities.- The Preparing for Pandemics channel brings together courses on various aspects of preparedness, including surveillance, public health measures and risk communication during a pandemic.- The COVID-19 channel provides learning resources in WHO's 6 official languages (Arabic, Chinese, English, French, Russian and Spanish) for health professionals, decision-makers and the public for the outbreak of coronavirus disease (COVID-19).- The COVID-19 National Languages channel provides the same learning resources as the COVID-19 channel but in national languages, such as Indonesian, Japanese and Portuguese. OpenWHO courses are available in many languages, including WHO's 6 official languages. Download the app now, and join the OpenWHO community.This app is developed in cooperation between the Hasso Plattner Institute and the WHO. The learning content is provided exclusively by the WHO.

title: AskFirst (formerly Ask NHS)
description: Ask NHS is now AskFirst. AskFirst provides you with improved access to health and care advice. You can talk through your symptoms in complete confidence with Olivia, a virtual health assistant.If needed, Olivia will arrange for a call back from a clinician to discuss your symptoms further. You can also search healthcare advice, schedule GP appointments and search opening times/locations of local healthcare services. Our service is available to all NHS patients in England over 16. Parents or guardians can create accounts on behalf of patients under 16 years of age.Please note for immediate life-threatening emergencies call 999.When to use AskFirst:- Abdominal pain- Back pain- Cough- Cold or flu symptoms- Chest pain- Dizziness- Fever- Headache- Pregnant and vomiting- Rash- Sore throat- Urinary symptoms- General medical questions, "Should I go in for this or not?"

title: DKV Quiero cuidarme Más
description: These are the functionalities that you can access from I want to take care of myself More, whether or not you are a DKV customer:• Health and wellness content from the “Home” screen to keep you up to date with the latest trends and topics of interest.• My diary: the summary of your recent activity and the most relevant information about your health management.• My health: from where you can keep track of your health indicators, such as physical activity, weight, blood pressure, among others; being able to connect with Apple Health, Google Fit, Garmin and Fitbit. In addition to being able to calculate your Healthy Life Index, a value that allows you to know if you lead a healthy lifestyle.• Challenges: where you can see and sign up for different challenges to improve your health, check your achievements and compare yourself with other users of the application.As a DKV client you also have access to:• DKV Club Salud y Bienestar: where you can enjoy discounts, raffles and promotions on health and wellness products and services. From I want to take care of myself More you can view offers and the reservations you have made.With a health policy, DKV Selection or DKV Famedic Professional, you can also access:• Consultations: from where you can search for the specialty you want and you will see all the possibilities of care, face-to-face or video consultation with professionals from the medical staff or the DKV Virtual Health Space by video, chat and voice (depending on the specialty). In addition, you will be able to check your symptoms.• My health: with the Folder section, to store and consult your health documents, such as clinical tests, prescriptions or medical reports. In addition, you can share your entire portfolio with our doctors so you can get their opinion on your reports and test results.In addition, you can use the services for your minor relatives included in the policyAnd exclusively for health customers:From Home you can access:• Digital card, you will no longer need to carry your insurance health card with you, because you will have it on your mobile, available from the Home section, in the upper left corner.• My pharmacy: in the "Featured" section, to request new prescriptions, view your medications and electronic prescription, as well as chat with a pharmacy professional to answer your questions. In addition, you will see the related discounts of the DKV Health and Wellness Club.• Take care of your mind: in the "Featured" section, in which we group information on the state of your mental health and the possibility of receiving psychological guidance to solve those issues that concern you. In addition, you will see the related discounts of the DKV Health and Wellness Club.In addition, you can also enjoy:• Consultations: where in addition to the above, you can also request a consultation with a Coach who will help you lead healthy lifestyle habits (quit smoking, lose weight, etc.). You can also consult with a digital midwife, who will advise you via chat about your health and that of your baby during pregnancy and postpartum. And you can also request information on second medical opinion.• My health: personalized prevention plans with which you can complete questionnaires, which will be evaluated by a health professional who will guide you.If you have questions, you can contact us at support@dkvservicios.comI want to take care of myself More is managed by DKV Servicios SA, which provides digital health services for DKV Seguros y Reaseguros SAE. Your data is treated securely in compliance with current legislation.

title: Mediktor
description: Solve your health questions from the first symptom.Check your symptoms for FREE.The symptom checker allows you to input how you feel with your own words. Its artificial intelligence picks the questions a professional would ask to get to a list of possible conditions and a recommendation.See the description of diseases in our dictionary.Please do not hesitate to send us your suggestions or comments: info@mediktor.comSpecs:- Artificial intelligence and natural language interpretation.-CE - 7074-PS LicenseMediktor is a sanitary licensed medical device. It complies with all the essential requirements and with the conformity assessment procedures that are applicable to it according to AEMPS and European Union regulations.This tool does not offer medical advice. It is provided for informational purposes only.Do not use it to replace professional medical advice, diagnosis or treatment.If you believe you may have a medical emergency, call your doctor or the Emergency Medical Services immediately.

title: HEALTHLYNKED COVID-19 Tracker
description: HealthLynked has developed its own Corona-virus tracker app that allows users to self-report symptoms, report positive tests for the virus, and alert contacts so that they can seek medical care to prevent spread. The app includes an interactive map of COVID cases and deaths from around the world, the latest worldwide COVID-19 related news, user forums, and live chat. in addition, you can learn about the Omicron variant and use an interactive map for the US.We continue to report the latest WHO data indicated by the following Criteria:WHO confirmed infections are shown in RED, WHO confirmed deaths are shown in BLACK. User can self-report and they are divided into three categories:Users that have NOT tested positive for the virus and are asymptomatic are shown as DARK GREENUsers that have NOT tested Positive for the virus but have symptoms such as a fever, cough or shortness of breath are shown as YELLOWUsers who Self Report that they have tested Positive for the Corona Virus are shown as PINKUsers can update their Information as symptoms change and these changes are reflected on the Map. The tracker also shows all the latest news about the virus from around the world to keep users updated on the Virus. Users can also engage in real-time chat with the chat feature. Data sources: COVID- USAFacts (https://usafacts.org/data-sources/)OMICRON- CDC (https://covid.cdc.gov/covid-data-tracker/#variant-proportions)Privacy Policy: https://www.healthlynked.com/privacy-policy/Terms of Use: https://www.healthlynked.com/terms-of-services/Contact Us: https://www.healthlynked.com/contact-us/

title: GVA Coronavirus
description: Aplicación móvil oficial de la Conselleria de Sanitat Universal i Salut Pública para solicitar cita con tu centro de salud en caso de presentar síntomas clínicos compatibles con infección por COVID-19.A través de la APP también se puede acceder a una amplia información sobre la infección causada por coronavirus COVID-19. Los síntomas compatibles con infección por COVID-19 son síntomas de infección de vías respiratorias, estando presente uno o más de los siguientes: - fiebre (más de 37º)- tos- estornudos- dolor de garganta - dificultad respiratoriaSi se han presentado estos síntomas en los últimos 14 días debes solicitar la cita mediante esta App.Si los síntomas que padeces revisten gravedad o tienes una emergencia llama al teléfono 112.Las citas a través de esta App están dirigidas a los casos posibles de infección COVID-19.La cita se solicita mediante la introducción de tu número SIP y la fecha de nacimiento, y realizando la confirmación del teléfono de contacto. Recibirás una llamada en el plazo máximo de 24 horas desde la confirmación de la creación de la cita. En el caso de no recibirse la llamada en el plazo de 24 horas se puede volver a realizar la petición mediante la App o mediante llamada al teléfono 900 300 555.A través de la App se te informará del estado de la cita: solicitada, confirmada, realizada. Si durante la primera llamada telefónica el profesional sanitario de tu centro de salud identifica tu caso como posible de COVID-19, el resto de citas telefónicas para efectuar el seguimiento de tu caso serán programadas por el profesional sanitario. A partir de ese momento, recibirás llamadas periódicas para verificar tu estado de salud y ayudarte en todas las dudas y necesidades que puedas presentar.Si presentas otros síntomas diferentes a los indicados, ponte en contacto con tu centro de salud a través de los teléfonos de cita previa habituales. La Conselleria de Sanidad Universal y salud Pública  es la responsable y autora de la información que se muestra en la aplicación, además, garantiza la privacidad y protección de tus datos (http://coronavirusautotest.san.gva.es/proteccion-datos-es.html). Asimismo, la Conselleria garantiza que se almacenará y utilizará la información personal de un modo suficientemente seguro, durante el tiempo necesario y solo para proporcionarte los servicios personalizados anteriormente descritos.Para salvaguardar la información de la persona usuaria/paciente, esta aplicación usa el protocolo seguro HTTPS para todas las comunicaciones con los servidores.

title: COVID-19.eus
description: COVID-19.eus es una aplicación colaborativa para gestionar la pandemia del COVID-19 en el ámbito de la comunidad autónoma vasca. La aplicación permite hacer un autodiagnóstico del contagio de COVID-19. En caso de ser positivo, el usuario se considerará POSIBLE contagio (según terminología de la OMS) y avisará a todo el círculo de personas, de tal forma que se considerarán en riesgo.Junto a esta información el sistema registrará ese dato, de tal forma que se puede seguir un rastro de contagios con esta funcionalidad de círculos. Se solicitará el Código Postal, y en caso de infección comunitaria, se podrían también detectar focos de contagio.Esta información es muy útil para un estudio epidemiológico.No se guarda ningún dato y los estudios serán anónimos y se podrán compartir con la Autoridad Sanitaria Vasca.A partir de la versión 3.1 se incluye la funcionalidad Empresas que permite a los empleados compartir, si así lo desean,  su estado con la Empresa.

title: Tonic: Medicina para Médicos
description: ¡Tonic App es gratuita y combina todos los recursos profesionales para la práctica clínica! Es un dispositivo médico certificado para toda Europa para garantizar la seguridad y calidad de sus calculadoras. Actualmente, Tonic solo está disponible para médicos, pero tenemos la intención de extender su uso a todos los profesionales de la salud y estudiantes. De momento no disponemos de recursos suficientes para adaptarnos a los diferentes colectivos con la calidad que estimamos necesaria. ¡Esperamos que lo entiendas!Diseñada por médicos, para médicos: grupos de discusión de casos clínicos, receta electrónica, Covid-19: información actualizada (artículos científicos, vacunas, webinars, consensos de sociedades médicas y protocolos del Ministerio de Sanidad), +50 calculadoras (inc. pediátricas)*, TNM, congresos, conversión de fármacos, vademecum, algoritmos de diagnóstico, tratamiento y derivación**, empleo médico y noticias semanales de salud.Estamos en constante mejora. Actualizamos nuestra app para responder a las necesidades inmediatas y reales del colectivo médico. Próximamente: videoconsulta, información para pacientes y CIE-10. *Dosis de antibióticos, brecha aniónica, calcio corregido en hipoalbuminemia, Child-Pugh, CRB-65, CURB-65, diámetro del tubo endotraqueal, dosis de antibióticos y antipiréticos, talla diana, escala de coma de Glasgow, edad gestacional, índice de masa corporal (IMC), colesterol LDL, MELD, mMRC, NIHSS (AVC), peso estimado pediatría, presión tobillo-brazo, score CRUSADE, Sheridan, área de superficie corporal, ecuación CKD-EPI, entre otras.**Algoritmos más utilizados en el último año: fibromialgia, depresión, amigdalitis, infección urinaria, diarrea, infecciones de la piel y de los tejidos blandos, neumonía, anemia y trombosis venosa profunda. ¡Publicamos una patología nueva todas las semanas!Útil para todas las especialidades: alergología, análisis clínicos, anatomía patológica, anestesiología y reanimación, angiología y cirugía vascular, aparato digestivo, bioquímica clínica, cardiología, cirugía cardiovascular, cirugía general y del aparato digestivo, cirugía oral y maxilofacial, cirugía ortopédica y traumatología, cirugía pediátrica, cirugía plástica, estética y reparadora, cirugía torácica, dermatología médico-quirúrgica y venereología, endocrinología y nutrición, estomatología, farmacología clínica, geriatría, hematología y hemoterapia, hidrología médica, inmunología, medicina de la educación física y el deporte, medicina espacial, medicina del trabajo, medicina familiar y comunitaria, medicina física y rehabilitación, medicina intensiva, medicina interna, medicina legal y forense, medicina nuclear, medicina preventiva y salud pública, microbiología y parasitología, nefrología, neumología, neurocirugía, neurofisiología clínica, neurología, obstetricia y ginecología, oftalmología, oncología médica, oncología radioterápica, otorrinolaringología, pediatría y sus áreas específicas, psiquiatría, radiodiagnóstico, reumatología y urología.Con Tonic App puedes:- Participar en grupos de discusión de casos clínicos o crearlos tú mismo- Pedir una segunda opinión profesional- Ponerte en contacto con otros colegas y ampliar tu red de contactos- Emitir recetas electrónicas y enviarlas al mail de tus pacientes- Usar calculadoras clínicas con garantía de seguridad- Consultar algoritmos de decisión realizados según las guías internacionales- Buscar fármacos y consultar tablas de conversión de medicamentos- Buscar congresos en todo el mundo- Estadificar a tus pacientes oncológicos con la clasificación TNM- Encontrar vacantes de empleo para médicos- Leer las noticias de actualidad sobre salud     El registro solo es necesario cuando se utiliza la aplicación por primera vez. Los datos que solicitamos durante el proceso sirven para verificar que eres médico.Tu opinión es importante. Puedes ponerte en contacto con nosotros en: soporte@tonicapp.com

title: BizkaiUp – Bizkaia en tu móvil
description: ¡Bienvenido/a a BizkaiUp!La app con la que podrás disfrutar de los mejores planes de turismo, agenda de actividades y tus noticias de interés. Ahora también la mejor atención ciudadana con nuestros nuevos servicios de cita previa.Cuando está abierta la temporada puedes reservar hora para el servicio de BAÑO ASISTIDO, y evitar posibles colas en la playa. Con este servicio, las personas con limitaciones en su movilidad y autonomía personal pueden disfrutar del baño en el mar - ¿Qué es BizkaiUp?-BizkaiUp es una aplicación de la Diputación Foral de Bizkaia que te permite acceder a la información más relevante de Bizkaia. Dispone de un servicio de notificaciones con el que estar al día de las novedades que se produzcan y un punto de contacto con Atención Ciudadana. Ahora, más que nunca, la actividad de Bizkaia está más cerca de quienes buscan disfrutar de nuestro territorio.Accede  a nuestro nuevo servicio de Atención Ciudadana. En este apartado podrás realizar consultas, encontrar teléfonos de interés y solicitar tus citas previas. Gestiona tus citas previas con la Diputación Foral de Bizkaia desde tu móvil. Nuestras apps donde accederás a todas las aplicaciones disponibles que tiene en la actualidad la Diputación Foral de Bizkaia, toda la información en la palma de tu mano.Nueva home más intuitiva y nueva sección “Mi espacio” donde vas a poder fijar secciones como favoritas para que puedas acceder a ellas de una manera mucha más rápida y te facilite el acceso. Si has solicitado una cita en nuestro apartado de cita previa, también podrás ver un resumen con la información básica de tus citas.En Bizkaup nos preocupamos por la accesibilidad, gracias al blanco y negro nuestra interfaz es más legible. Bizkaiup ahora disponible en light mode y dark mode. - ¿Cómo darte de alta en BizkaiUp y empezar a disfrutar de sus servicios?-Es muy fácil, solo tienes que usar el sistema  Bak o BakQ que ya conoces,  tras lo que podrás acceder a servicios avanzados con la Diputación Foral de Bizkaia.¡Si no tienes la Bak o BakQ no te preocupes, puedes consultar cómo conseguirla desde BizkaiUp!.Ahora ya puedes disfrutar de tu día a día con BizkaUp, vive Bizkaia.————— Descarga BizkaiUp app hoy —————¿Dudas o comentarios?¡Nos encanta leer vuestras opiniones! ¿Tienes alguna sugerencia?No dudes en ponerte en contacto con nuestro equipo de profesionales escribiéndonos un email a bizkaiup@bizkaia.eus¡Únete a los miles de usuarios que ya utilizan BizkaiUp!Si te ha gustado la experiencia de BizkaiUp no olvides mandar tu valoración.
developer: Bizkaiko Foru Aldundia–Diputación Foral de Bizkaia

title: TousAntiCovid
description: Let’s protect our loved ones, ourselves and everybody else with TousAntiCovid.# Stay informedIn TousAntiCovid, you can follow the situation regarding Covid. # TousAntiCovid WalletWith the Wallet, you can add your COVID-19 certificates (vaccine and test) digitally into the app, for best convenience.And you can have your favorite certificate in a Widget, or on your Apple Watch!# My data is protected Data is stored locally on your iPhone. You can delete the data stored on your iPhone from the TousAntiCovid settings, whenever you want._TousAntiCovid is designed for use in France.The application has been developed by the TousAntiCovid team under the supervision of the Ministère de la Santé et de la Prévention and the Secrétariat d'Etat chargé du Numérique.

title: AarogyaSetu
description: Aarogya Setu is a mobile application developed by the Government of India which connects the various essential health services with the people of India. The application is playing a crucial role in our combined fight against COVID-19 and now, has evolved as the National Health application to serve the people of India in an exemplary way. The application has come up with an intuitive User Interface and comprehensive features such as ABHA (Health ID) creation, discovery & linking of health records to enable longitudinal digital health records, Simplified Consent Management for sharing these records, and a Seamless Search feature to find Nearby Hospitals, Labs and Blood Banks.

title: توكلنا (Covid-19 KSA)
description: تطبيق توكلنا هو التطبيق الرسمي المعتمد بالمملكة العربية السعودية للحد من انتشار فايروس كورونا، وتم تطويره من الهيئة السعودية للبيانات والذكاء الاصطناعي "سدايا".ساهم تطبيق توكلنا في بداية إطلاقه بإدارة منح التصاريح إلكترونيًا خلال "فترة حظر التجوال" للقطاع الحكومي والقطاع الخاص وكذلك الأفراد، مما ساعد في الحد من انتشار فيروس كورونا في المملكة.وخلال مرحلة العودة بحذر، أطلق التطبيق عِدّة خدمات جديدة مهمة تساهم في تحقيق العودة الآمنة، أبرزها توضيح الحالة الصحية لمستخدم التطبيق من خلال الأكواد المُلوَّنة بأعلى درجات الأمان والخصوصيَّة.

title: TGN Emergències
description: The City Council of Tarragona offers citizens an application that gives you updated information about the emergency issues in Tarragona and about the safety and protection measures that must be taken.

title: Estadão
description: Baixe e conheça o aplicativo do Estadão, que traz o melhor conteúdo para o seu dia a dia, de forma ágil e com credibilidade:Leia notícias em tempo real, análises, artigos de especialistas e checagem de fatos.Receba alertas das notícias mais importantes.Personalize a seção Para Você, só com os assuntos do seu interesse.Assista a uma seleção de vídeos, mesmo com o app fechado.Siga os seus colunistas favoritos para não perder nenhuma análise.Salve as notícias e leia na hora que quiser.Encontre o conteúdo mais atualizado sobre eleições, economia, saúde, empreendedorismo, notícias internacionais, cultura, esportes, sustentabilidade, bem-estar e muito mais.Vem pensar com a gente!Termos de uso: https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/

title: Conecte SUS
description: O Conecte SUS Cidadão é o aplicativo oficial do Ministério da Saúde, onde o cidadão brasileiro pode visualizar as interações realizadas nos pontos de atenção à saúde e acompanhar o seu histórico no Sistema Único de Saúde (SUS), como exames, vacinas, dispensação de medicamentos e localização de estabelecimentos de saúde. O cenário de risco à população provocado pela pandemia do novo Coronavírus exigiu respostas contundentes de todo o sistema de saúde, em especial do SUS, para coordenar as ações nacionais e orquestrar os esforços de estados, municípios e, também, da Saúde Suplementar. Diante disso, o Conecte SUS, a partir da implementação da Rede Nacional de Dados em Saúde (RNDS), foi redirecionado para receber e compartilhar informações que auxiliem no controle da situação de emergência da saúde pública, com destaque ao processo de vacinação Covid-19 no Brasil.Funcionalidades:Acesse os resultados de exames realizados por qualquer laboratório no território nacional integrado à RNDS para a detecção da Covid-19;Veja seu histórico de vacinação na Carteira de Vacinação Digital;*No momento, o Conecte SUS apenas apresenta os dados relacionados à vacinação contra a Covid-19, especificando a data da aplicação, o nome da vacina, o lote, o estabelecimento de saúde e o código do vacinador. Gradativamente serão disponibilizadas as demais vacinas ministradas pelo SUS.Emita o Certificado Nacional de Vacinação Covid-19 na palma da mão. Após as duas doses da vacina (ou a dose única) serem registradas pelos estados ou municípios na RNDS¹, é possível emitir o certificado em pdf nos idiomas português, inglês e espanhol. Esse documento é válido em todo território nacional e pode ser autenticado gratuitamente, utilizando o leitor ValidaQRCode no próprio aplicativo ou digitando o código do documento em: https://validacertidao.saude.gov.br/;*No certificado é especificado os dados cadastrais da pessoa vacinada (nome, data de nascimento, sexo, CPF), data e horário de emissão, além de informações sobre as doses administradas, como a data de aplicação, nome da vacina, lote e estabelecimento de saúde. Acesse o histórico de internação hospitalar no SUS;*Dados a partir de abril de 2018.·      Veja os medicamentos dispensados pela Farmácia Popular;Localize rapidamente os estabelecimentos mais próximos como os serviços de Saúde Bucal e Doenças Raras;Consulte dicas nutricionais e de atividades físicas e verifique o Índice de Massa Corporal (IMC) na funcionalidade “Peso Saudável”; Quer saber mais?Acesso o Conecte SUS na web em: https://conectesus-paciente.saude.gov.br/Acesse os portais:https://www.gov.br/saude/pt-br/assuntos/conecte-sushttps://www.gov.br/pt-br/servicos/certificado-nacional-de-vacinacao-covid-19https://www.gov.br/saude/pt-br/assuntos/saude-digitalhttps://www.gov.br/saude/pt-br/assuntos/rnds¹ Os registros são de responsabilidade dos gestores estaduais e municipais de saúde, que fazem a coleta e envio das informações para a base de dados do Ministério da Saúde. Eles são feitos pelas equipes responsáveis do centro de vacinação ou da unidade de saúde onde a dose foi aplicada. Os dados são inseridos nos sistemas de informação próprios ou integrados à RNDS, no Sistema de Informações do Programa Nacional de Imunizações (SI-PNI) ou Sistema e-SUS Atenção Primária à Saúde (s-SUS APS). Após os dados enviados e processados, são inseridos de forma automática no Conecte SUS, que está disponível pelo celular ou na versão web.

title: Coronavirus UY
description: Información, atención médica, y alertas de exposición a COVID-19 para residentes en Uruguay.Utilizando Coronavirus UY podrás conseguir toda la información actualizada acerca de la enfermedad en Uruguay, y de cómo proteger tu salud y la de tu familia.En caso de tener alguno de los síntomas podrás realizar consultas directamente a través de la aplicación y, si fuese necesario, tu prestador de salud podrá coordinar para que se te realice un test.Activando las Alertas de Exposición, tu teléfono podrá avisarte si detecta una posible exposición al virus, para que recibas asesoramiento, seguimiento y atención lo más rápidamente posible. El sistema es operado y gestionado por la Agencia de Gobierno Electrónico y Sociedad de la Información y del Conocimiento (Agesic) y el Ministerio de Salud Pública del Uruguay (MSP), en el marco del Plan Nacional Coronavirus.En el caso de contraer la enfermedad, la aplicación te permitirá informar diariamente a tu médico acerca de tu estado de salud (por ejemplo fiebre u otros síntomas). De esa forma podrá mantenerse al tanto de tu salud, indicarte la mejor forma de cuidarte, e incluso contactarte a través de videollamadas.Permite gestionar el seguimiento de tu grupo familiar, registrando en tu propio dispositivo a tus hijos u otras personas a cargo.Nota: las Alertas de Exposición solo están disponibles en teléfonos iPhone con iOS versión 12.5, o bien 13.5 o superior.

title: Majadahonda en tu móvil
description: Toda la información del municipio en la palma de tu mano. Busca y pulsa… ¡Así de simple! Noticias: Consulta la actualidad de tu municipio y comparte lo que te interesa por email, WhatsApp o RRSS (Facebook y Twitter) Agenda:  Espectáculos culturales, actividades de la biblioteca, eventos deportivos, cursos de emprendimiento, escuela de padres y talleres para todos. Si te interesa una obra de teatro, concierto o espectáculo, podrás comprar las entradas desde tu móvil, a través de Giglón. Incidencias:Participa e infórmanos sobre cualquier incidencia que detectes enviando una fotografía con geolocalización y un breve texto sobre el problema, y haremos todo lo posible por solucionarlo. Revista Cultural:Descarga la programación cultural completa, en formato PDF, y/o accede al portal de Cultura. Todos los portales a un clic:Accede la web del Ayuntamiento, comprueba los resultados de la jornada en el portal de Deportes, participa en Majadahonda Joven o consulta la programación de fiestas.  Enlace al Portal Tributario:Facilitamos los trámites administrativos de impuestos y autoliquidaciones de tasas. Durante el periodo voluntario puedes consultar recibos, pagar con tarjeta y obtener la carta de pago. Instalaciones:Localiza las infraestructuras más relevantes de la Administración. El Auditorio Municipal, la Escuela Infantil Talín, El Centro de Salud Cerro del Aire, el Registro Civil… todo aparece en el mapa. La APP conecta con tu navegador y te lleva donde quieras ir. Directorio:¿Necesitas el teléfono de una farmacia? ¿Dónde está el Centro de Mayores? ¿Te interesa la web de un colegio o escuela infantil? ¿Buscas la dirección de un polideportivo? Encuentra lo que buscas, pulsa, y podrás llamar por teléfono, enviar un email, acceder a la web informativa o abrir el navegador para que te lleve a tu destino.

title: COVID Symptom
description: An easy-to-use app to track and record COVID-19 symptoms.There is no fee to use this app.In this time of crisis, every resident of the world is anxious about getting COVID-19, and views every sneeze, every cough, and fever as a sign that they may have COVID-19. Governments of every country are concerned about the spread of COVID-19, and are in search of solutions to help their citizens, and understand and prevent the spread of COVID-19.Are you anxious about COVID-19?Are you having fever, cough, or other symptoms?Have you been tested for COVID-19?Have you had contact with someone with COVID-19?Does a family member or friend have COVID-19?Do you want to contribute towards COVID research?In an attempt to solve these issues, we have built this COVID-19 symptoms tracker. Here are the key things you can do with this app:- Track key COVID symptoms- See history of your symptoms- Help alleviate anxiety- Help scientists and researchers to track, study, and model prevalence of COVID-19 in our communities- Share a report of your symptoms with your doctor- Maintain a record of your COVID-19 test resultsWe have a well-researched list of COVID-19 related symptoms which can be tracked.Please note this app does not provide medical advice. If you have severe symptoms, please call 911, call your doctor, or go to the hospital emergency room.This app is currently not advised for use by people who are hospitalized with severe symptoms.Data Security:Your personally identifiable information, such as email ids and phone numbers will not be shared with anyone. We do not track your location, and do not collect or store any location data, except for a country and postal code that you can optionally enter. Your Donated Data will be made available to researchers.We may use aggregated, Donated Data to create heat maps showing prevalence of symptoms in the community, in order to help the public and policy makers better understand the spread of COVID-19.For questions and support, please contact help@covidsymptom.orgYou can also share this COVID symptoms tracker app with your friends and family to help them track their symptoms, contribute to COVID research and join our fight against COVID-19.Let's all unite and help each other out to fight this pandemic.If you would like to volunteer to help this project, please contact "volunteer@covidsymptom.org"

title: Coronavírus - SUS
description: O Ministério da Saúde do Brasil lança o app Coronavírus-SUS com o objetivo de conscientizar a população sobre o Corona Vírus COVID-19, para isso o aplicativo conta com as seguintes funcionalidades:- Por conta da funcionalidade de contact-tracing o aplicativo é compatível apenas em Iphone versào 13.5 ou superior.- Informativos de diversos tópicos como os sintomas, como se prevenir, o que fazer em caso de suspeita e infecção e etc;- Mapa indicando unidades de saúde próximas;- Em caso de suspeita de infecção, o cidadão pode conferir se os sintomas são compatíveis com o do Corona, e caso seja será instruído e encaminhado para a unidade de saúde básica mais próxima;- Área de notícias oficial do Ministério da Saúde do Brasil com foco no Corona Vírus.

title: Bioscientia Travel Pass
description: Die neue Travel Pass-App der BioscientiaPush-Mitteilung erhalten, Testergebnis prüfen, grenzenlos reisen - mit der neuen Travel Pass-App können Sie Ihr Labor-Testergebnis schnell und sicher mit nur einem Klick von unterwegs abrufen und auf Ihre Reise mitnehmen.# So funktioniert esNachdem Sie Ihre Auftragsdaten in der App eingegeben und bestätigt haben, werden diese mit den Befunddaten Ihres Bioscientia-Labors abgeglichen. Nach erfolgreicher Verifizierung und medizinischer Validation wird Ihnen ihr Labor-Testergebnis durch die App in Form eines PDF-Zertifikats inklusive Befund bereitgestellt. Wenn Sie möchten, informiert Sie automatisch eine Push-Nachricht darüber.# Travel Pass-ScanDurch die Travel Pass-Scan Funktion haben Sie alternativ auch die Möglichkeit, eine Barcode-Grafik oder einen QR-Code zu scannen, um Ihre Auftragsdaten einzugeben.# Travel Pass-SignaturMit Travel Pass-Signatur können Sie auf Wunsch Ihr persönliches Testergebnis mit Ihrer Personalausweisnummer oder mit Ihrer Reisepassnummer signieren. Dadurch wird ihre Ausweisnummer direkt auf dem PDF-Zertifikat dargestellt. Für die Einreise in manche Länder ist es erforderlich, dass Ihr negatives Testergebnis mit Ihrer Ausweisnummer (Personalausweis oder Reisepass) signiert ist.# SicherDie Travel Pass-App ist unser innovativstes und sicherstes Verfahren um Ihnen Ihre Laborergebnisse direkt zur Verfügung zu stellen. Die App bietet die größtmögliche Sicherheit durch ein modernes Kommunikations-Verfahren mit zweifacher Verschlüsselung. Ihre eingegebenen Daten werden ausschließlich zur Identitätsprüfung genutzt. Die App speichert keine zusätzlichen Daten.# VoraussetzungenDiese App ist ausschließlich in Verbindung mit Auftragsdaten von einem Labor der Bioscientia-Gruppe verwendbar!
developer: Bioscientia Institut für Medizinische Diagnostik GmbH

title: CovPass Cyprus
description: The official application of the Cypriot Government where EU citizens can download the EU Digital COVID Certificate aimed at facilitating safe free movement of citizens in the EU during the COVID-19 pandemic. The COVPASS app works with full security of personal data. The EU Digital COVID Certificate was created to allow Member States to adjust their present public health restrictions to facilitate cross-border travel for their citizens.An EU Digital COVID Certificate is a digital proof that a person has either • been vaccinated against COVID-19• received a negative test result or • recovered from COVID-19The general features of the EU Digital COVID Certificate are:• Available in a digital and/or printed version• With QR code• Free of charge• Available in Greek and English• Secure, protected and authenticated• Privacy of personal data• Available in Greek and EnglishFor further information please contact the Call Center at 1474 for Cypriot numbers and +357 22 285757 for foreign numbers or via email at info@eudcc.gov.cy
developer: Deputy Ministry for Research, Innovation & Digital Policy

title: Unidos Contra el Covid
description: Bienvenido a la aplicación #UnidosContraElCovid, en la que encontrarás información oficial referente a los síntomas, la prevención y la vacunación contra el virus COVID-19 en Bolivia.También accederás a la información más relevante para la prevención y contención del virus, como ser el costo de los medicamentos, el costo de servicios médicos, o a contactarte con un médico en línea.

title: Plan Jalisco Covid-19
description: “Plan Jalisco Covid-19”, es una herramienta tecnológica que hace posible verificar a las autoridades si los usuarios han tenido contacto con personas que padecen del coronavirus y/o han estado expuestos a condiciones y/o lugares que pudieren representar un “contacto cercano” con el virus.“Plan Jalisco Covid-19”, también brinda a sus usuarios información sobre los síntomas y/o prevención del virus COVID-19 con la finalidad de ayudar a evitar su propagación, y poder detectar si están siendo afectados por la enfermedad y obtener recomendaciones. La aplicación también permite a las autoridades, la geolocalización de sus usuarios, siempre que activen esta funcionalidad, con el objetivo de establecer el debido contacto y seguimiento de los casos de aquellas personas sospechosas y/o infectadas por el Síndrome Respiratorio Agudo Severo Coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) denominado COVID-19, y lograr una respuesta más ágil y eficaz en cada caso particular.El contenido y/o el uso de la aplicación está orientada exclusivamente a informar a todas las personas sobre el virus COVID-19, es importante aclarar que las recomendaciones, lineamientos, sugerencias o guías que puedan encontrarse en la aplicación no constituyen opinión médica ni deben utilizarse para realizar un diagnóstico ni iniciar un tratamiento médico sin la consulta de un profesional de la salud.“Plan Jalisco Covid-19”, no sustituye la opinión médica.Adicionalmente, el Gobierno del Estado de Jalisco podrá incluir funcionalidades en la aplicación que permitan mejorar la asistencia e información del virus COVID-19.

title: TraceTogether
description: TraceTogether supports Singapore’s efforts to fight the spread of COVID-19 through community-driven contact tracing.TraceTogether notifies you quickly if you’ve been exposed to COVID-19 through close contact with other TraceTogether users. The app allows the Ministry of Health (MOH) to give you timely care and guidance, protecting you and those around you.The app uses Bluetooth, and your Bluetooth data is stored securely on your phone. It’ll be shared with MOH if you test positive for COVID-19, for the purpose of contact tracing. Also, all Bluetooth data stored on your phone is automatically deleted after 25 days.TraceTogether helps us ensure that we don’t spread the virus to our loved ones unknowingly. It also helps us support the work of contact tracers and healthcare workers by combating the spread of COVID-19 together.App functionality will cease once the outbreak ends.TraceTogether is designed for use by people in Singapore. To register, you will need a valid NRIC, FIN, or a valid document of your current stay in Singapore.

title: patientMpower for COVID-19
description: The patientMpower for COVID-19 app is for people in the Republic of Ireland who have been enrolled in the COVID-19 remote monitoring programme by a healthcare professional. The patientMpower for COVID-19 app will allow you to monitor your COVID-19 symptoms and health information such as your oxygen levels and temperature whilst you are in self-isolation. This information will be shared confidentially with  trained personnel at dedicated monitoring centres. They will be able to see your information immediately. Monitoring will enable healthcare professionals to assess if you are recovering well whilst in isolation or if you need additional support (e.g. extra treatments at home or if you need to go to hospital). It is recommended that you consent to using location services after downloading this app. If you don’t want to consent to sharing your location you can continue to use the app. The location information will be de-identified and used for research into COVID-19. KEY FEATURESMonitors your oxygen saturation (using a device called a pulse oximeter), which is important to track to ensure you are recovering from COVID-19Tracks your symptoms including breathlessnessRecords details of relevant underlying conditions and your existing medicationsAnonymised location monitoring, to help us understand trends of COVID-19 across Ireland and plan resources to best deliver healthcareSyncs with Apple Healthkit to track heart rate and activityConfidential health data viewable in real time by healthcare professionals at monitoring centrespatientMpower are an Irish digital health company who are experienced in providing home monitoring  platforms for people with lung conditions. If you need help installing the app or need any technical support please email support@patientMpower.com. IMPORTANT: This app cannot provide medical intervention in the event of an emergency. If you experience a rapid worsening of symptoms or severe breathing difficulties please contact 999 or 112.

title: CoronaSurveys
description: The CoronaSurveys project is a collaborative research project involving several universities and research institutions. Data about COVID-19 cases is collected via anonymous open surveys. The main questions we ask are: How many people do you know personally in this geographical area?How many of the above have been diagnosed or have had symptoms compatible with COVID-19, to the best of your knowledge?From these people, how many have recovered?We collect no personal information and all the data collected is openly available to researchers. Our results  provide estimations on the incidence of COVID-19 based on the data we collect and other available data. Please help us by regularly completing the anonymous survey. By completing this simple survey you are making it possible improve our understanding of the outbreak.

title: CDC
description: Get the official CDC Mobile application to access the most up to date health information.FILTERING OPTIONSOrganize your home screen so that the information that’s most important to you appears first! Turn off the content you don’t want with just a flip of a switch and reset it all with the tap of a button.CONTENTThe app ensures that you’re getting the most up to date health information. The home screen lets you see all your information in one place and updates whenever your device is connected to WI-FI. Enjoy a greater variety of content such as Disease of the Week, disease case counts, videos, podcasts, and features to give you the most current health information from CDC. Browse Featured Articles, stay on top of health news in the Newsroom section, and view CDC Images of the Week. If you’re a journal reader, view the latest Morbidity & Mortality Weekly Report, Emerging and Infectious Disease journal, or the latest on Preventing Chronic Diseases. You can even search CDC’s web content from the app.  We'd love to hear your thoughts about the app! Rate the CDC Mobile App in the App Store or leave a comment to let us know how we're doing. You can even send us an email through the app if you have suggestions for improvements!DISCLAIMERTHE MATERIALS EMBODIED IN THIS SOFTWARE ARE PROVIDED TO YOU "AS-IS" AND WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESSED, IMPLIED OR OTHERWISE, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION, ANY WARRANTY OF FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE CENTERS FOR DISEASE CONTROL AND PREVENTION (CDC) OR THE UNITED STATES (U.S.) GOVERNMENT BE LIABLE TO YOU OR ANYONE ELSE FOR ANY DIRECT, SPECIAL, INCIDENTAL, INDIRECT OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES OF ANY KIND, OR ANY DAMAGES WHATSOEVER, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION, LOSS OF PROFIT, LOSS OF USE, SAVINGS OR REVENUE, OR THE CLAIMS OF THIRD PARTIES, WHETHER OR NOT CDC OR THE U.S. GOVERNMENT HAS BEEN ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH LOSS, HOWEVER CAUSED AND ON ANY THEORY OF LIABILITY, ARISING OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE POSSESSION, USE OR PERFORMANCE OF THIS SOFTWARE.
developer: Centers For Disease Control and Prevention

title: أمان - الأردن كوفيد-١٩
description: تطبيق أمان مصمم للاستخدام داخل المملكة الأردنية الهاشمية فقط وسوف يتم إزالته من المتجر بعد انتهاء وباء فايروس كورونـا (كوفيد-١٩) بإذن اللهتطبيق أمان هو تطبيق للهواتف الذكية يحمي الخصوصية، وبنفس الوقت يعمل على تنبيه المستخدمين في حال تم الاشتباه بتعرضهم لفيروس كورونا (كوفيد-19) ومخالطتهم لشخص مصاب، وذلك من خلال استخدام تقنية  الـ(GPS)، وقريباً البلوتوث. تم تطوير تطبيق "أمان" كمبادرة مجتمعية لصالح وزارة الصحة من قبل COVID-19 JOTECH COMMUNITY، وهي مجموعة من الخبراء الأردنيين المقيمين والمغتربين العاملين في قطاع تكنولوجيا المعلومات والذين تطوعوا بخبراتهم ومهاراتهم لمساعدة الأردن بجهود احتواء فيروس الكورونا. يهدف تطبيق أمان كشف التعرض للفيروس باستخدام تقنية نظام التموضع الجغرافي (GPS)، الأمر الذي يجعل عزل حالات الاصابة بفيروس كورونا المستجد أسرع وقبل أن تسبب العدوى للآخرين، مما يؤدي إلى احتواء الفيروس وضمان سلامة مستخدميه وعائلاتهم ومجتمعهم.خصوصية بياناتكم هي أولوية، تماماً كصحّتكم. لذلك، يقوم تطبيق أمان بتخزين البيانات على جهازكم فقط ولا يطلب منك أي معلومات شخصية أو بيانات يمكن أن تؤدي إلى تحديد هويتك أو انتهاك خصوصيتك. يتم استخدام بيانات الموقع المخزنة على هاتفك لغرض واحد:  تتبع واحتواء فيروس كورونا المستجد. ويتم مسح بياناتك تلقائيا كل 14 يوماً (فترة احتضان الفيروس) ولن يكون من الممكن استعادة تلك البيانات المخزنة. وفي حال الإصابة بالفيروس، يمكن للمريض وبموافقته تصدير البيانات المخزنة على هاتفه ومشاركتها بشكل مجهول الهوية مع باقي المستخدمين عن طريق مسؤولي وزارة الصحة. وعند وجود إشعار بنقطة التقاء عند شخص ما، لا يعلم هذا الشخص من هو المصاب أو الذي كان قريبا منه، ويُطلب منه الاتصال مع الخط الساخن لوزارة الصحة وطلب فحص للفيروس.لمزيد من المعلومات عن مبادرة تطبيق أمان المجتمعية، يرجى زيارة موقع وزارة الصحة: www.corona.moh.gov.jo و www.amanapp.jo

title: 3EP
description: COVID-19 testing app - for guided, supervised and documented selftest with supported tests kits - providing a documented proof of the performed tests and the achieved results.For further information and to watch the short instruction video please visit our page at https://3ep.appFor the use of the app the user required the 3EP QR-codes, as well as supported test kitsTo use this COVID-19 Testing App, the user will have to provide his consent that the app is getting access to the following resources, when the app is in use: - Camera / VideoPurpose:  For tracking and documenting the test process when performing a test as well as to identify the test person when performing a test or presenting a test certificate- Audio and Microphone Permissions - Audio and Microphone Permissions are required to access the Camera functionalities in the Android Operating System. No Audio data or data from the microphone is being collected or processed.- Location (at postal code / city level when performing a test)Purpose: to identify the responsible healthcare organization and the local COVID-19 rules in case of a positive test.We process the following personal data for the purposes of your unique identification, validation of test performance, and issuance of test certificates: - User account information (such as username, unique user ID, etc.)- Contact information (such as residence address, email address, phone number)- Basic personal information (e.g., name, date of birth, country of residence)- Biometric information (e.g., facial recognition)- Proof of identity (e.g., number and type of ID card you used to identify yourself. An image of your ID card will be taken for identification processing and will be deleted after processing)- Documentation pictures taken of you during the testing procedure All personal data is stored exclusively in encrypted form in the App on your smartphone. Personal data is not shared with digitales.services AG (the publisher of the 3EP app) nor with any other 3rd party.Only in the event that a transmission of positive test result to the local or central health authorities is legally required in the country / region where the test was performed, this will be done through the APP on your smartphone via a data interface or an email, depending on the requirement of the respective health authority. You will also receive an email from us to the email address you provided with the information from the relevant health authority and a link to the local health information that you must follow in this positive test case. This is comparable to COVID-19 test performed in a test center and you have to provide your consent to that when using the app.or view our instruction video at https://youtu.be/o6mgV0LJ0Ls

title: Covid19 QR verify
description: Ковид-19 вакцины QR код шалгах аппликэйшн.

title: COVID19 Sounds
description: The aim of this research is to collect data to inform the diagnosis of COVID-19 by developing machine learning algorithms, based primarily on sounds of their voice, their breathing and coughing.In order to enable this research we are launching a large scale, crowdsourced data collection from healthy and non-healthy participants through an application. The app will collect some basic demographics and medical history data, as well as some voice samples (while you read text on the screen) through a questionnaire and a few seconds of breathing and coughing through the phone microphone. We will additionally collect one location sample. The app will also ask if you have tested positive for the virus.The app won't be tracking you and only collect this data when you actively interact with it. The data will be stored on University servers and be used solely for research purposes. We hope to release the dataset we are collecting to other researchers after the initial analysis and pre-processing. The app will not give medical advice and any reports of symptoms will not be responded to by medical assistance.

title: COVID-19: Staying Safe
description: ‘Covid-19 Staying Safe’ from Starfish Labs, helps people with learning difficulties and disabilities to understand the Coronavirus pandemic guidelines and regulations. It features simple guides to wearing a face covering, hand washing and sanitising, and keeping the home clean. Content can be viewed and created in English or Welsh. The app includes guidance developed in collaboration with educationalists from a leading UK special educational needs college.To make the content highly relevant to the individual’s own understanding or level of learning difficulty, the app features the ability for admin users (e.g. a parent, carer or teacher) to upload your own content relevant to the individual – using images of their own face coverings, their own washing facilities etc. in their own home, school, college or work environment. This makes the app highly effective in conveying information that is recognisable and relevant for individuals who may not identify with generic information that does not show specific items in their own environment.Using this app you can easily create a new guide to any aspect of rules and guidelines under Covid-19 that are relevant to the user’s own circumstances, your local lockdown tiers, or regional variations in guidance during the pandemic. Your custom content is stored on your own device and does not require WiFi to access it once you have downloaded the app.In the general guidelines content, the app uses simple cartoons, photographs, videos, voice and Makaton symbols to convey information in an easy-to-understand format. The content can be viewed in English or Welsh.The images and videos feature real people with learning difficulties demonstrating how to wear different types of face covering, how to dispose of single-use masks, wash re-usable face coverings, how to wash your hands properly, how to use hand sanitiser and clean your home environment to help to stay safe.The content is based on general UK Government guidelines and has been developed, simplified and tested in collaboration with staff, residents and students at Derwen College – an Ofsted Excellent rated Special Educational Needs College. The app uses Makaton symbols - © The Makaton Charity - with Makaton content supplied by the college.This app has been part funded by Welsh Government. Starfish Labs acknowledge the support of Welsh Government and Derwen College in the creation of this app. All imagery, graphics, voice content, workflow system and development © Copyright Starfish Labs 2020.

title: RA & COVID-19
description: This app offers a 30 minute module on RA and COVID-19 as well as two screencasts on  Safe Remote Assessment of MSK Conditions and Safe DMARD Prescribing and COVID-19 and finally a Podcast talking about Holistic Care for Patients with RA.
developer: The Royal College Of General Practitioners

title: Путешествую без Covid-19
description: Приложение "Путешествую без Covid-19" позволяет находить лаборатории рядом с вами для сдачи анализов на Covid-19 перед путешествием между Российской Федерацией, Республикой Армения, Республикой Беларусь, Республикой Узбекистан, Республикой Казахстан, Кыргызской Республикой и Республикой Таджикистан.  При пересечении границы покажите QR-код с результатами анализа уполномоченному сотруднику, имеющему право запрашивать результаты ПЦР-теста в соответствии с национальным регулированием.

title: COVID19VMI
description: Este aplicativo serve especificamente para o manejo médico e de equipe multiprofissional nos casos de COVID-19 das Unidades de Terapia Intensiva e Hospitais de Retaguarda.Permite uma navegação rápida e intuitiva de algoritmos de decisão clínica e procedimentos críticos da ventilação mecânica invasiva e manejo de drogas, centrado na segurança dos pacientes e equipe multiprofissional.Não se destina a pacientes, e não recomenda automedicação.Esta iniciativa da equipe Atlantes contou com o apoio e supervisão da UTI Respiratória do INCOR-HCFMUSP e da Secretaria de Saúde do Governo do Estado de São Paulo.
developer: Hospital das Clinicas da Faculdade de Medicina da Universidade de Sao Paulo

title: Lector COVID
description: Para un registro rápido de los síntomas de COVID - 19Los alumnos registran diariamente sus síntomas y presentan el código QR generado desde el sitio https://covid.isie.mx.Se utiliza esta aplicación para leer el código QR y registrar rápidamente los síntomas de cada alumno, acelerando el proceso de detección de brotes de infección a nivel salón de clase, grado o escuela.El encargado podrá revisar los síntomas reportados por el alumno y registrar cualquier cambio en los mismos desde que se hizo el chequeo inicial, después procederá a dejar entrar al alumno al recinto o mandarlo a casa. Una advertencia se mostrará en la pantalla de la aplicación cuando los síntomas coinciden con los reportes de posible infección por COVID 19.Desde https://covid.isie.mx el personal del colegio puede obtener reportes detallados de los síntomas de cada alumno registrado y notificar a las personas que tuvieron contacto con el alumno.IMPORTANTE: Esta aplicación únicamente funciona en colegios afiliados a ISIE en su programa de registro de síntomatología de COVID 19

title: iHelp Sunshine Coast
description: Information and support to help you locate the services most useful to you in a crisis situation. Input user information to get refined results of service providers that can help with your specific needs. Use the information tab to gain an understanding of what different services can do for you and what to expect. Use the search tab to locate services in your area and access them quickly and easily. Use this app if you or someone you know need assistance accessing important services to stay safe and improve well-being.

title: COVID-19 Timor-Leste
description: The situation changes often. Stay up to date with the latest information about the spread of COVID-19 and the steps being taken to slow the spread in Timor-Leste.

title: COVID-19: Happy & Healthy
description: ‘Covid-19: Happy & Healthy’ from Starfish Labs helps people with learning difficulties and disabilities and their carers to explore ways to stay Happy and Healthy during the Covid-19 pandemic and beyond, complementing the other apps in this series: Covid-19: Staying Safe and Covid-19: Social Space. Content can be viewed in English or Welsh. Although aimed at people with learning difficulties the content is equally applicable to anyone who wants to live a more healthy lifestyle – both during and beyond the Covid-19 pandemic. Users can work through the simplified content alone or with a friend, parent, teacher or carer, and access the more detailed resources and links as a source of ideas for activities in the key areas of:• Staying Well• Eating Well• Being Active• Sleeping Better• Avoiding risky substances• Looking After Your FeelingsThe guidance on staying healthy in body and mind has been developed in collaboration with a UK Public Health GP Champion for Physical Activity along with simplified guidance and Makaton symbol content developed, simplified and tested in collaboration with staff, residents and students at Derwen College – an Ofsted Excellent rated Special Educational Needs College.In the general guidelines content, the app uses simple cartoons and Makaton symbols © The Makaton Charity - with Makaton content supplied by Derwen College, to convey information in an easy-to-understand format.This app has been part funded by Welsh Government. Starfish Labs acknowledge the support of Welsh Government and Derwen College in the creation of this app. All imagery, graphics, voice content, workflow system and development © Copyright Starfish Labs 2021.

title: Terr-eSanté eCovid
description: Terr-eSanté eCovid est disponible UNIQUEMENT pour les personnes suivies par les professionnels et établissements de santé utilisateurs de Terr-eSanté eCovid.Terr-eSanté eCovid est un dispositif de suivi à distance ou télé-suivi, adapté au COVID-19., il vous permet de :- consulter et renseigner un questionnaire médical, défini par les professionnels de santé qui vous prennent en charge ;- accéder aux coordonnées et contacter simplement les professionnels santé de votre cercle de soins ;- consulter des informations utiles sur le COVID-19 ;- contacter le support utilisateurs.Pour y accéder, vous devez disposer d’un compte Terr-eSanté. L’accès à l’application mobile se fait avec les mêmes identifiants que le site web Terr-eSanté (www.terr-esante.fr/patients).Terr-eSanté eCovid est une application dédiée aux patients. Une application mobile dédiée aux professionnels de santé est également disponible (Terr-eSanté PRO App)eCovid est un module intégré à Terr-eSanté, la solution régionale de coordination de soins entre les acteurs de santé franciliens. Terr-eSanté met le patient au cœur du dispositif de soins, et lui offre différents services en ligne (gestion de son cercle de soins, partage de documents avec son équipe soignante, réception automatique sécurisée de ses documents type comptes-rendus et résultats de laboratoire, suivi d’objectifs…) parmi lesquels s’inscrit eCovid.Terr-eSanté eCovid, est une application mobile portée par l’Agence Régionale de Santé d’Île-de-France et mise en œuvre par le GCS SESAN.

title: Gateway COVID-19 Response
description: The gateway app includes a daily assessment which securely and safely collects actionable data in real time per any individuals reporting to Gateway Academy. Items pertaining to COVID-19 symptoms, exposure and testing along with the intention to report to school are tracked and displayed in real time to aid administrative functions. The app also acts as a communicative tool between the school administration and parents.

title: SAFE HealthCheck
description: Get the care you need, when you need it, where you need it.Our Digital Health and Connected Diagnostics platform makes it easy to connect with a doctor for a virtual appointment from the comfort of your home. You can also order home test kits, have your results scanned using your smartphone, and have your prescription sent straight to your pharmacy. Whether you have insurance or not, we can help you get the care you need. Feature Highlights-Virtual care appointments -Order home test kits-Scan your results using your smartphone-Prescriptions sent to your pharmacy -24/7 support whenever you need-Vaccination verification-Remote patient monitoring-We offer a variety of payment optionsBenefits-Convenient and easy to use-Personalized care plans-Affordable-SecureWe're here to help you stay healthy, no matter where you are. Please reach out to us at safecdx.com if you are a business looking for virtual care solutions. —-Please note that telehealth is not for emergencies. If you’re having a medical emergency, call 911.

title: BMC Combat Covid19
description: Work with BMC to fight the spread of COVID-19. We encourage you to download this app, and mark your position for self quarantine. This will help us track your health progress and contain the spread of this virus.

title: Alivio Coronavirus
description: ALÍVIO CORONAVIRUS é um jogo educacional voltado para o aprendizado sobre o coronavírus e a doença que causa, o Covid 19.É destinado a profissionais da saúde (médicos, fisioterapeutas, psicólogos, enfermeiros), pacientes diagnosticados com a doença e a população em geral. A sua dinâmica é baseada nas respostas (certas ou erradas) que o jogador dá ao ser inquirido sobre os mais diversos temas relacionados ao coronavírus, e a doença que causa, o Covid 19. Vencer o jogo, então, depende de acertar mais do que errar. O jogador pode optar por jogar na seção GERAL (para os ADULTOS) ou na seção FAMÍLIA (para as CRIANÇAS).No ponto de partida, o jogador ainda está hipoteticamente assintomático. Daí em diante ele percorre um caminho de casas cujo fim da linha é o Covid 19 em grau severo ou grave. O ir e vir do ícone do jogador ao longo desse percurso é governado, primeiro, pelos seus acertos ou erros ao qualificar afirmações sobre dor como Certas ou Erradas; e segundo, pelo arbítrio de uma roleta acionada após o jogador ser informado do seu resultado ao responder cada pergunta. Os pontos que a roleta indicar determinam a movimentação para cima ou para baixo do ícone no percurso. Ele cai na direção do Covid 19 em grau severo ou grave, e sobe na direção oposta, a da cura definitiva.Ao longo do percurso, e dependendo de onde o ícone pousar, há também imprevistos, ou seja, fatores aleatórios que podem atrasar ou apressar a movimentação do jogador por esse caminho.O jogo permite enfrentar um competidor virtual e somente termina quando o jogador vence ou perde em definitivo. O banco de perguntas geral é suficientemente robusto, considerando que a conhecimento científico sobre o tema ainda é limitado. O tempo do jogo, dependendo da seção escolhida, pode variar aproximadamente entre 30 minutos e 2 horas.

title: MyGy Pro
description: MyGy Pro è un’app veloce e intuitiva creata da un team di esperti e pensata per la pratica clinica sia di ginecologi esperti che di giovani specialisti.Le tematiche trattate sono la Ginecologia e l’Ostetricia con particolare riferimento alle nuove tecnologie diagnostiche e chirurgiche. L'app mostra le possibili diagnosi e terapie da intraprendere per la cura della patologia evidenziata.

title: KI-COVID19
description: This App enables participation in a survey to assess the spreading of COVID-19 among students and teachers in the university campus. It also provides access to relevant information on protection against infection and related policies. The collected data will be used for evaluation of the effects of on-campus teaching during the pandemic.

title: COVID-19: Social Space
description: ‘Covid-19: Social Space’ from Starfish Labs helps people with learning difficulties and disabilities to understand Social Distancing guidelines and regulations. It features simple guides to social distancing, support bubbles, indoors and outdoors guidelines and video information on social distancing in public places, complementing the first app in this series: Covid-19: Staying Safe. Content can be viewed and created in English or Welsh. The app includes guidance and Makaton symbol content developed in collaboration with educationalists from a leading UK special educational needs college.Using this app you can also easily create a new guide to any aspect of rules and guidelines under Covid-19 that are relevant to the user’s own circumstances, your local lockdown tiers, or regional variations in guidance during the pandemic. Your custom content is stored on your own device and does not require WiFi to access it once you have downloaded the app.To make the content highly relevant to the individual’s own understanding or level of learning difficulty, the app features the ability for admin users (e.g. a parent, carer or teacher) to upload your own content relevant to the individual – using images of their own support bubble, types of signs they might see, how far apart people should stay etc. in their own locality and their own home, school, college or work environment. This makes the app highly effective in conveying information that is recognisable and relevant for individuals with learning difficulties who may not identify with generic information that does not show specific items in their own environment.In the general guidelines content, the app uses simple cartoons, videos, voice and Makaton symbols to convey information in an easy-to-understand format. The video features real people with learning difficulties demonstrating social distancing in real-life situations, with reminders about wearing masks, hand washing, hand sanitisers and surface cleaning to help to stay safe.The content is based on general UK Government guidelines and has been developed, simplified and tested in collaboration with staff, residents and students at Derwen College – an Ofsted Excellent rated Special Educational Needs College. The app uses Makaton symbols - © The Makaton Charity - with Makaton content supplied by the college.This app has been part funded by Welsh Government. Starfish Labs acknowledge the support of Welsh Government and Derwen College in the creation of this app. All imagery, graphics, voice content, workflow system and development © Copyright Starfish Labs 2021.

title: Natl COVID-19 Resiliency Net
description: Morehouse School of Medicine’s National COVID-19  Resiliency Network (NCRN) provides awareness to critical health information & linkage to services, helping families recover from difficulties caused or worsened by the COVID-19 pandemic. NCRN is part of a cooperative agreement with the U.S. Department of Health & Human Services Office of Minority Health.  Grant #1CPIMP201187-01-00
developer: The Morehouse School of Medicine, Inc.

title: Corona-Care
description: CoronaCare es una plataforma diseñada para ayudar a los prestadores de atención médica, empresas gubernamentales y empresariales a rastrear los síntomas de COVID-19 de pacientes potencialmente infectados; desarrollada conjuntamente con algunos de los principales sistemas de salud como Mass General Hospital y Harvard Medical.Esta plataforma es utilizada directamente por pacientes que han sido examinados en una clínica o sala de emergencias y son enviados a casa, incluye una aplicación para pacientes para rastrear si las personas han cambiado de grupos de bajo a alto riesgo, así como para proporcionar instrucciones y precauciones para tratar los síntomas. El portal de proveedores permite a los prestadores clasificar los casos de los pacientes por gravedad y mitigar los riesgos de propagación pública al proporcionar a todos los pacientes conocimientos y recursos para tratar los síntomas de bajo riesgo en el hogar, al tiempo que rastrea el desarrollo de síntomas en pacientes de mayor riesgo.Esta aplicación permite ayudar a los pacientes a quedarse en casa si no son de alto riesgo, pero no brinda consejos de salud. Si necesita consejos de salud, visite el sitio web de los CDC en:  https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-nCoV/index.htmlNo se utilizará información con fines comerciales y todos los datos están encriptados.Características: •	Mitigue los riesgos de propagación pública al proporcionar a todos los pacientes conocimientos y recursos para tratar los síntomas de bajo riesgo en el hogar.•	Seguimiento del desarrollo de síntomas en pacientes de mayor riesgo a través de encuestas personalizadas.•	Los prestadores pueden registrar a los pacientes dándoles un código QR específico de la institución para escanear y descargar la aplicación.•	Integrado con Fitbit, Withings, HealthKit, CCD, CDA, DICOM, HL7, FHIR y portales de pacientes.•	Módulo de inscripción masiva a través de mensajes de texto para invitaciones de registro de población.•	Encuestas preliminares y de seguimiento se enviarán al paciente a través de la aplicación.•	Los resultados de la encuesta de pacientes aparecerán en el portal del proveedor (Centro de comando) y se codificarán automáticamente por color según la gravedad del caso.•	Las encuestas se pueden enviar a grupos objetivo con frecuencias específicas a través de notificaciones automáticas, correos electrónicos o mensajes de texto.•	Proporciona instrucciones a los pacientes en la aplicación.•	Mensajes instantáneos bidireccionales y videollamadas entre prestadores y pacientes.•	Cuenta con un chatbot habilitado con IA para ayudar a los pacientes con preguntas de manera más efectiva

title: Preworkscreen
description: Get back to work as fast as possible with Preworkscreen’s online system for managing your employee’s COVID-19 symptom self-assessments. Let your employees use mobile phones to perform their own COVID-19 symptom assessments and have Preworkscreen keep you informed about your workforce’s overall health status.• Stay compliant with state (NY, CA, NJ, etc.) reopening employee self-assessment guidelines and reduce your company’s liability risks• Keep your business safe by letting employees self-screen using symptom assessment questionnaires based on state orders and CDC guidelines before entering work• Protect your employee’s health and business’s environmental safety by preventing the spread of COVID-19 at your offices and worksites• Avoid the burdensome task of manually administering, collecting, and documenting your employee’s COVID-19 symptom screenings• Quickly find out the health status of your workforce using Preworkscreen’s company dashboard and report generation system• Let Preworkscreen automatically store your employee’s self-assessment submissions and all the other information you need to prove state order and guideline compliance• Keep in touch with your employees using a company hotline designated for reporting COVID-19 issues• Stay up-to-date by letting Preworkscreen worry about updating your screening procedures as state orders and guidelines change

title: Cachoeirinha ContraCoronavírus
description: Panorama AtualAcompanhe o panorama de casos na nossa cidade em tempo real.Checagens DiáriasFaça checagens diárias dos sintomas do Coronavírus em sua família.Proteja-seProteja sua família mantendo a Secretaria de Saúde informada dos casos e auxilie no controle ao COVID-19.

title: Corona Expert
description: The purpose of Corona Expert app is to share the latest news and helpful information expressed as Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) related to the current COVID-19 outbreak.  In addition to the FAQ, you can test your knowledge through a trivia-style experience and check the facts about COVID-19. Corona Expert app is provided by Silverberry Genomix, a leading digital health platform that uses AI and machine learning to optimize health and wellness decisions in partnership with Dana-Farber Cancer Research Institute. For more information about the app visit https://silverberrygenomix.com/coronavirus/

title: 연세 COVALT
description: 연세대학교 COVALT 는 연세대학교 학생 및 교직원을 위한 애플리케이션으로, 교내 방역 보조를 위해 개발되었습니다.세브란스병원의 자문을 받아 제작된 COVID-19 자가진단 설문과, 강의동이나 기숙사 출입 시 간편하게 QR 코드 스캔으로 체크인할 수 있는 기능을 제공합니다.

title: Managing your stress & anxiety
description: This app provides information and evidence-based coping strategies to help you manage stress and anxiety during the COVID-19 pandemic. It is not intended to be a resource for people who require screening for COVID-19 or are experiencing a mental health crisis. If you are experiencing a mental health crisis, please contact 911 immediately or present to your nearest emergency department.The Centre for Addiction and Mental Health (CAMH) is Canada's largest mental health teaching hospital and one of the world's leading research centres in its field. CAMH is fully affiliated with the University of Toronto and is a Pan American Health Organization/World Health Organization Collaborating Centre.
developer: Centre for Addiction and Mental Health (CAMH)

title: Odisha COVID Dashboard
description: This is an informative app for citizens regarding Corona status. An initiative from Government of Odisha for the citizens.

title: Biolink Companion
description: Companion app for Biolink’s EcoTest COVID-19 Rapid Antigen PensThe Biolink companion app supports our easy-to-use, non-invasive technology that enables rapid and accurate testing in professional and home environments.It contains step-by-step instructions, help with record keeping, video guides and contact information.

title: Ustar PortNAT
description: The APP provides users to browse and view the testing process description of USTAR PortNAT series products. Users can complete the relevant testing and save the test results according to the guidelines.[Disclaimer]Any information content on this platform is only used for information purposes, and does not involve/replace professional medical advice or medical professional diagnosis; Before making any medical decision in the process of using this platform, please seek the doctor's advice first.[Declaration of Jurisdiction]At present, the medical hardware has obtained the regulatory certification license of EU and Australia, and can be used in EU member states and Australia.

title: FioLibras
description: FioLibras é um app para pessoas surdas e profissionais de saúde, produzido pela Fiocruz, com informações confiáveis e atualizadas sobre o novo coronavírus e a pandemia da COVID-19, disponíveis na Língua Brasileira de Sinais (Libras), com legendas e narração em português. O aplicativo é gratuito e não é necessário fazer nenhum cadastro para acessar. Para acessar os vídeos em Libras sobre a COVID-19, basta fazer uma busca por palavras em português ou navegar pelas categorias e saber mais sobre: O que é COVID-19, Fake News (Notícias falsas), Prevenção, Sintomas, Transmissão, Diagnóstico, Tratamento, Vacina, Grupos de risco, Notícias, Pesquisas científicas e Bem-Estar na Pandemia. Clique em um vídeo para selecionar e assistir em tela cheia. Para marcar um vídeo como “Favorito”, clique no ícone de estrela. Se você gostar desse aplicativo, conte para seus amigos e amigas e ajude-nos a levar essas informações para outras pessoas surdas. Caso tenha alguma dúvida ou sugestão, entre em contato conosco, enviando uma mensagem ou um vídeo em Libras pelo app.

title: Karantinas
description: Programėlė „Karantinas“ yra skirta kasdieniam koronaviruso simptomų sekimui, prevenciniams veiksmams skatinti ir saviizoliacijos priežiūrai.
